In a preliminary report released by SAPS, the business robbery at a shopping centre in Parow occurred at about 3.30pm on Tuesday. "According to reports two unidentified males entered the cellular telephone shop, they were positively armed and they threatened the employees," police spokesperson FC van Wyk said. "They took an undisclosed amount cellular telephones andÂ fled the scene. Whilst fleeing from the scene they shot and wounded one person in the arm. It is unknown what type of vehicle was used to flee from the mall.  "Our Crime Scene investigators is still on the scene investigating."    Anyone with more information that can assist with the investigation is kindly requested to contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111. Cape Argus  